      "text": [
        ": فِي اِمْرَأَةٍ قَتَلَتْ رَجُلاً مُتَعَمِّدَةً فَقَالَ \"إِنْ شَاءَ أَهْلُهُ أَنْ يَقْتُلُوهَا قَتَلُوهَا وَ لَيْسَ يَجْنِي أَحَدٌ جِنَايَةً عَلَى أَكْثَرَ مِنْ نَفْسِهِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5225 - Abu Usamah narrated from Abdullah ibn Sinan from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a woman who intentionally killed a man.\nImam (as) said: \"If the family of the murdered person wishes to kill her, they may do so. No one bears the burden of a crime beyond their own soul.\""
        ]
      }
